    <div class="col-sm-6">
        <h1>1937</h1>
        <p>Red dot - New York City, United States, 1937- George Stibitz proved that boolean logic could
           be used in computers through his Model "K" Adder circuit, which utilized electromechanical relays.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
