        </figure>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-6">
        <h1>1938</h1>
        <p>Blue dot - Berlin, Germany, 1938- Konrad Zuse finishes the Z1 computer, the first computer in
            the world. The Z1 operated on Boolean logic. This prototype, along with Z2 and Z3, was destroyed during WWII.</p>
        <p>Red dot - Mansfield, United States, 1938- Elektro, a smoking, walking, and talking robot, is
            finished in Ohio by Westinghouse. Elektro was voice controlled, although the voice commands were understood by their rhythm- the robot did not understand their meaning. Elektro was demonstrated in the 1939 World's Fair in New York with great success.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm-6">
