    <div class="col-sm-6">
        <h1>1939</h1>
        <p>Blue dot - Berlin, Germany, 1939- Konrad Zuse develops the Z2. This computer was relay-based
            as an improvement on the Z1, which did not work very well. It was almost done in 1939, but it was delayed to 1940 due to Zuse being required to join the army.</p>
        <p>Red dot - New York City, United States, 1939- George Stibitz produces the Model I Complex
            Calculator, the first electrical digital computer. It built on the boolean logic circuits
            Stibitz created. This computer utilized telephone switches and electromechanical relays.</p>

    </div>
